<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-100-532  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 100 532.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Network World  March 6 1989 v6 n9 p19(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Federal Express net supports global cause.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Crockett, Barton.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Federal Express has experienced both success and failure in itsuse of communications technology.andP;  Its COSMOS package trackingsystem allows customers to find out where their package is at anystep of the delivery process, invaluable information for firmsthat use Federal express for just-in-time delivery and a featurewhich has earned the firm greater margins on domestic packagedelivery than most of its competitors.andP;  But its ZapMail facsimileventure, begun in 1984, ended in 1986 with a loss of $340 million.andO;Acknowledging the volatility in the telecommunications market,Federal express will concentrate on short-term contracts in thatarea, and will look to expanding its international shippingbusiness for the long term.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Federal Express Corp. (planning).andO;Ticker:    FDX.andO;Topic:     TransportationGrowthPlanning.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>